SIMPLE: extroversion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: extroversion
<hw>ex`tro*ver"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Extrorse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of being turned
wrong side out; <as>as, <ex>extroversion</ex> of the bladder</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>the trait of being interested
primarily in things in one's external environement, rather than one's
own thoughts and feelings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>the act of directing one's
interests primarily toward things in one's external environement, rather
than one's own thoughts and feelings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>extroversive</ent>⟦br⟧
